RA2_GameSounds/aprotr1.mp3.transcription: Join the Allies! We have hot food, women, and guns for everyone!

RA2_GameSounds/aprotr2.mp3.transcription: Start a new life with the allied forces! You'll get all the bread and milk you could ever want!

RA2_GameSounds/aprotr3.mp3.transcription: Join the winning side. Be a pioneer of freedom for the new Soviet democracy.

RA2_GameSounds/aprotr4.mp3.transcription: Free TV's for all who join us! Act now! Freedom is yours for the taking!

RA2_GameSounds/aprotr5.mp3.transcription: Bring us the fat and lazy! Come join in the decadent lifestyle of the West!

RA2_GameSounds/icfasec.mp3.transcription: I like a man in uniform.

RA2_GameSounds/icfsmoa.mp3.transcription: I'll be late for bread line.

RA2_GameSounds/ichrfea.mp3.transcription: I don't have time for this.

RA2_GameSounds/icisatb.mp3.transcription: For it to come in good.

RA2_GameSounds/icisatc.mp3.transcription: I feel too, as you say.

RA2_GameSounds/icraatc.mp3.transcription: I lost a bomb! Do you have it?

RA2_GameSounds/icramof.mp3.transcription: I don't want to kill someone that way.

RA2_GameSounds/idesatf.mp3.transcription: Let's make an oasis of death!

RA2_GameSounds/idesmoe.mp3.transcription: It will be a silent spring.

RA2_GameSounds/ienapow.mp3.transcription: We'll have the power up in 30 seconds, sir.

RA2_GameSounds/ienspow.mp3.transcription: we will have the power up in thirty seconds sir

RA2_GameSounds/iflafea.mp3.transcription: I can't see through a flock!

RA2_GameSounds/irocata.mp3.transcription: He's got no place to hide!

RA2_GameSounds/iseasec.mp3.transcription: A little C4 knocking at your door.

RA2_GameSounds/isnimob.mp3.transcription: Just give me a clear view.

RA2_GameSounds/iyursee.mp3.transcription: The mine is quicker than the eye.

RA2_GameSounds/vdematc.mp3.transcription: It will be a smoking crater!

RA2_VoiceLines/ceva047.mp3.transcription: Enable to comply, building and progress.

RA2_VoiceLines/ceva081.mp3.transcription: Fire power technology stolen. All units gain fire power upgrade.

RA2_VoiceLines/ceva082.mp3.transcription: Armor technology stolen. All units gain armor upgrade.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau06.mp3.transcription: The V3 is a powerful long-range artillery weapon. Beware, Commander. It can level your base in minutes without you ever getting a chance to even return fire.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau07.mp3.transcription: The most powerful Soviet tank ever built. The apocalypse is a small army all by itself and is equipped to handle both ground and air threats.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau08.mp3.transcription: The most powerful air unit ever created. The cure-off can take a beating and drop an almost unlimited number of heavy iron bombs.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau13.mp3.transcription: The ultimate and Soviet long-range bombardment, the Dreadnought is powerful from a distance but can be easily destroyed at close range. The Dreadnought's missiles can also be shot down by Patriot missiles.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau15.mp3.transcription: The Soviets have taken Tesla technology to the final step, a man in a Tesla powered suit. These soldiers are excellent at destroying tanks and also seem to be able to power up Tesla coils with their extra energy.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau19.mp3.transcription: This soldier is equipped with a nuclear battle suit. He can irradiate large patches of ground making them impassable to infantry or light vehicles.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau20.mp3.transcription: The Soviets have been experimenting with psychic technology with some success. Their elite cycore can cause our own loyal soldiers to turn against us.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau22.mp3.transcription: This, sir, is our IFV. It is a multi-purpose raider capable of boosting the standard weapon capabilities of any infantryman inside.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau23.mp3.transcription: Sir, this is an engineer. He can repair any allied building. And once inside an enemy building, turn it to our side. He is much smarter than his Soviet counterpart.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau24.mp3.transcription: Sir, the seal is the elite soldier. No enemy is safe from him, whether on land or water.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau25.mp3.transcription: Commander, the spies ability to mask himself as the enemy and pass through their ranks gives him the needed edge to infiltrate even the most well-guarded enemy building. If only they didn't taste so good to Soviet dogs.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau26.mp3.transcription: The rocketeers are the brave men who strap maneuvering thrusters to their backs and then go out to hunt enemy tanks and air forces. They are very brave.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau27.mp3.transcription: Commander, this is a Chrono Legionnaire. Using Professor Einstein's Chrono technology, they teleport next to any enemy and utterly erase them from time.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau31.mp3.transcription: Commander, our Mirage tanks ability to hide itself among any natural objects around it make it the perfect ambush or covert surveillance vehicle.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau36.mp3.transcription: Commander, our destroyer is the workhorse of the Navy. No naval unit can long hide from it, and once detected, it makes short work of the enemy.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau37.mp3.transcription: Commander, there is no airborne threat that can evade the sight or missiles of the Aegis cruiser. It is the premier anti-air weapon.

RA2_VoiceLines/cevau38.mp3.transcription: Sir, our aircraft carriers are the pride of the Allied Navy. In a moment's notice, the carrier's planes can take out any target quickly and from a very safe distance.

RA2_VoiceLines/csof002.mp3.transcription: Warning, you play our missile launched.

RA2_VoiceLines/csof006.mp3.transcription: I and the curtain are ready.

RA2_VoiceLines/csof047.mp3.transcription: unable to comply, building and progress.

RA2_VoiceLines/csof081.mp3.transcription: Fire power technology stolen. All units gain firepower upgrade.

RA2_VoiceLines/csof082.mp3.transcription: Armor technology stolen. All units gain armor upgrade.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu04.mp3.transcription: Soviet technology at its finest. Terror drones can enter and destroy enemy vehicles from the inside.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu06.mp3.transcription: The V3 launcher has extreme range capabilities coupled with devastating damage potential. Distraction guaranteed. Just don't leave it undefended.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu07.mp3.transcription: The appropriately named Apocalypse Tank is war in a can. It can attack any ground or air targets and be expected to be their last unit standing.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu08.mp3.transcription: They may be slow, but the cure of airships can take great punishment and deliver even more.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu09.mp3.transcription: The sea scorpion is a fast attack sea raider. It cannot win the war for you, but you cannot win the war without it. It is your only anti-air defense on the war.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu10.mp3.transcription: I don't agree with this kind of experimentation, but you cannot deny the results. A giant squid can immobilize and eventually destroy any sea vessel.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu11.mp3.transcription: The typhoon attacks up is undetectable by normal allied units, but look out for allied dolphins and destroyers.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu15.mp3.transcription: The Tesla troopers have powerful weapons, but they are useless against buildings. They also make excellent base defense as they can overpower Tesla coils with their weapons.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu16.mp3.transcription: The Soviet engineer can repair buildings or capture enemy buildings if you can get them past defenses.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu18.mp3.transcription: Crazy Ivan can plant bombs on enemy buildings, or perhaps a conscript would agree to carry them for you.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu19.mp3.transcription: The allies cannot match our nuclear power. Deploy the desolator to sterilize an area.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu20.mp3.transcription: Our most top secret weapon, the Sycor, is useful for quickly turning allied units to other side.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu21.mp3.transcription: Commander, this allied GI is a well-trained soldier capable of quickly deploying a heavy machine gun when stationed within buildings or deployed with his sandbag nest.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu25.mp3.transcription: These arrogant allied spies believe that their disguises will allow them to infiltrate our buildings. They will soon find that the only thing they can infiltrate is our faithful dog's stomachs.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu26.mp3.transcription: The all-eyed rocket here is a man who hurled themselves through the air thanks to some jet-packs chopped to them in the hopes of wounding one of our tanks of buildings. Fools.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu27.mp3.transcription: Commander, beware these chronology-generators. They use some unknown technology to teleport themselves anywhere and then simply erase our forces.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu30.mp3.transcription: Comrade, this prison tank of the Allies is a dangerous threat to our must forces. Its directed energy weapon has no trouble harming many of our forces in a single shot.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu31.mp3.transcription: Another annoying trick of the Allies. The Amirash tank can mask itself as almost any object nearby it and then remain concealed and fire upon us.

RA2_VoiceLines/csofu33.mp3.transcription: The Allied intruder is an airborne threat to any of our forces who do not have adequate anti-air support. It does not stand up well to FLAC, Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev01.mp3.transcription: Don't forget, sir. Order Tanya as you see fit, but we cannot afford to lose her. You must reach Fort Bradley before it is destroyed.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev02.mp3.transcription: Looks like the bridge has been blown. We'll have to find another way to Fort Bradley.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev03.mp3.transcription: The Soviet Navy is attacking the Statue of Liberty. We can't let them get away with that. Sir, is there anything you can do?

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev04.mp3.transcription: Doesn't sound good, sir. We're going to have to double time at the rest of the way to reach Fort Bradley in time.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev05.mp3.transcription: Congratulations! We've re-established contact with Fort Bradley. They're turning over control of the base and its troops to you.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev06.mp3.transcription: We seem to have lost power, sir. Build more power plants.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev07.mp3.transcription: Looks like the bridge is collapsed, we'll have to get our engineers to repair it.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev08.mp3.transcription: Watch out for those petroleum barrels. They seem highly unstable. Perhaps we could use them to our advantage.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev09.mp3.transcription: Our GIs are too exposed to enemy fire. Maybe they should take shelter in nearby buildings.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev10.mp3.transcription: Sir, I'm sorry to report that we've lost Tanya.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev11.mp3.transcription: There's the supply base. Destroy all of the buildings and we'll buy some time for the rest of the country.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma1ev12.mp3.transcription: We've done it sir, the supply base has been eliminated.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma2ta01.mp3.transcription: Alright, this bacon's neutralized! Send in the cavalry!

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ev01.mp3.transcription: You can check one missile off your list, sir. That bird will never fly again.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ev02.mp3.transcription: Sir, we've managed to capture one of the silos instead of destroying it. Why don't we just turn it against the other missile silo?

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ev03.mp3.transcription: If you can get a spy into one of the Tesla generators, he can probably shut down all of the base's power for a good 30 seconds.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ev04.mp3.transcription: I'm resizing your radar to compensate for the nuclear missile coordinates that we just received. Stand by.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ev05.mp3.transcription: Sir, you just blew up the Soviet battle lab. Without the missile silo coordinates, we can't complete our mission.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ev06.mp3.transcription: Congratulations, sir. With both nukes neutralized, the European Alliance can join the war. We may have just changed the course of history.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5i101.mp3.transcription: Thanks for rescuing us, sir. Our plane was shot down by Soviet anti-aircraft. There's probably more survivors around here.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5i201.mp3.transcription: Glad you found us there. We're freezing out here.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5i301.mp3.transcription: Good to see you, sir. What are our orders?

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5i401.mp3.transcription: Beyond a lookout for spies, comrade, it seems a little too quiet tonight.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5i501.mp3.transcription: Heh heh. We don't need to worry about stupid American spies. That's what the dogs are for.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ta01.mp3.transcription: Looks like we're gonna need some more spice, sir.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ta02.mp3.transcription: Sir, could you send some more spies without neon camouflage this time?

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ta03.mp3.transcription: Looks like spies are becoming an endangered species. Send some more.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma5ta04.mp3.transcription: Crutch on a shingle mucking, suckin' son of a-- Oh, sorry, sir, but we need some more spies.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma6ev01.mp3.transcription: Hey, that's not Lincoln. They've put a Stalin head on him.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma6ev02.mp3.transcription: Sir, several of our vehicles have been eaten by terror drones. Our service depot can remove the drones and save our vehicles.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma7ev01.mp3.transcription: Commander, Nihao Island has fallen. We should prepare the rest of Hawaii for invasion.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma8ia01.mp3.transcription: Can't concentrate. Voices in my head. Victory to the Soviet Union!

RA2_VoiceLines/ma8ia02.mp3.transcription: Victory to the South! We're free! Get 'em!

RA2_VoiceLines/ma8ta01.mp3.transcription: Must reach the beacon just a little bit farther long live the glorious people's Soviet state.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma9se01.mp3.transcription: We're going to need some help getting through those defenses.

RA2_VoiceLines/ma9se02.mp3.transcription: Hot tamale! That's no Mayan pyramid! That's a prism cannon!

RA2_VoiceLines/ma9se03.mp3.transcription: Sir! These freedom fighters want to join up!

RA2_VoiceLines/maaei01.mp3.transcription: What does this button do? Please don't touch the auxiliary controls professor. They notify the commander of important events.

RA2_VoiceLines/maaei02.mp3.transcription: Commander, look out! They are over here! Professor, please stay off this channel.

RA2_VoiceLines/maaei03.mp3.transcription: Get these, Commander! Here they are here! Professor Einstein, I'm sure the Commander sees that.

RA2_VoiceLines/maaei04.mp3.transcription: You should seize this, Commander! Professor, if you touch the controls again.

RA2_VoiceLines/maaev05.mp3.transcription: Sir, if you build and deploy a spy satellite, you will be able to see the entire combat area.

RA2_VoiceLines/maaev06.mp3.transcription: We're rather low on resources in this location, sir. Perhaps you should construct an ore purifier so we can get more out of what we have.

RA2_VoiceLines/macev01.mp3.transcription: Attempting to jam all calls for help from Soviet command, but a few got through. Heavier Soviet reinforcements arriving soon.

RA2_VoiceLines/macev03.mp3.transcription: Intercepting broadcast from Soviet command. Romanov's panicking, sir. He's called for an air evacuation. The transports will arrive in two minutes.

RA2_VoiceLines/macev04.mp3.transcription: Soviet evacuation transports arriving in one minute.

RA2_VoiceLines/macev05.mp3.transcription: Soviet evacuation transports arriving in 30 seconds.

RA2_VoiceLines/macev06.mp3.transcription: Sir, Romanov is calling for evacuation again, he's trying to escape.

RA2_VoiceLines/macev07.mp3.transcription: Soviet units are defecting to our side.

RA2_VoiceLines/macis01.mp3.transcription: We will never surrender! Death to the Allies!

RA2_VoiceLines/macta01.mp3.transcription: We can't let Romanov get away.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so01.mp3.transcription: Commander, this is the first step in our glorious conquest. Victory here is crucial. Remember, we must crush the Pentagon. Above all else, the Pentagon must be destroyed.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so02.mp3.transcription: We cannot let a mere bridge delay our conquest commander or their engineers to enter the bridge's control station.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so03.mp3.transcription: Commander, pay no heed to casualties. For every conscript who dies in this crusade, there are a thousand more who stand eager to replace him.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so04.mp3.transcription: Commander, you can order your conscripts into nearby buildings to fortify them against the enemy.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so05.mp3.transcription: The pentagon is finally within our grasp. Destroy it immediately.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so06.mp3.transcription: Ah! Our comrades have decided to lend us support. These reinforcements, commander, are some of our most useful vehicles, flag trucks. Their speed, armor, and ability to carry infantry are the perfect support for our legions of conscripts.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so07.mp3.transcription: Superp Commander! The Pentagon has been destroyed!

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so09.mp3.transcription: Our base is out of power. We must build mod generators to bring our radar and defenses back online.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so10.mp3.transcription: Be wary of those barrels of petrol, if damage they will surely explode violently. Perhaps we can use them to our advantage.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so11.mp3.transcription: Capture the airport commander, in order to allow paratroopers to land in the area.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so12.mp3.transcription: Excellent comrade commander. As soon as the paratroopers are completely prepared, we will be able to strike anywhere you desire.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms1so13.mp3.transcription: The building that you have just discovered is one of America's special civilian buildings. Use an engineer to convert the building and gain its powers.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms3ca07.mp3.transcription: I will obey the Soviet... Where am I?

RA2_VoiceLines/ms3so01.mp3.transcription: Welcome to New York commander. Capture the allied battle lab at the World Trade Center and use the technology to build the psychic beacon.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms3so02.mp3.transcription: The beacon is placed, Commander, but it needs time to charge. Keep the allies from destroying the beacon.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms3so04.mp3.transcription: Excellent commander! Now use our new conscripts to deal with the remaining allied forces.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms4so02.mp3.transcription: I have displayed the estimated time remaining until the Allied fleet arrives commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms4so03.mp3.transcription: The Allied air forces are threatening our position. Deploy our flag cannons and they will turn the enemy's air units into scrap metal.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms5te01.mp3.transcription: Get me close to the tower, and I'll take care of the rest commanders.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms7so01.mp3.transcription: Sources have reported that Allied troops are messing outside the ochronosphere, a squat has just been teleported.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms7so02.mp3.transcription: Another enemy platoon has been teleported by the Chronosphere.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms7so03.mp3.transcription: One last allied platoon has been teleported by the Chronosphere.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms8so01.mp3.transcription: Now that the beacon is destroyed, the Americans are free from Vladimir's mind control.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms8so02.mp3.transcription: Destroy monuments to receive a cash bonus from Moscow.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9pr02.mp3.transcription: You, Sylvie, it's scum! You'll never take me!

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9pr04.mp3.transcription: You don't want the Vice President running the country, do you?

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9se01.mp3.transcription: Get the President outta here! Go, go, go!

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9so01.mp3.transcription: Intelligence reports that there is another bridge south of your position.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9so02.mp3.transcription: Yuri is en route to your position. Clear out the enemy defenses for his arrival.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9so03.mp3.transcription: Careful not to destroy the bunker commander. We want the president alive for interrogation.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9so04.mp3.transcription: The President is on the rescue ship. Sing the ship and we will fish him from the water.

RA2_VoiceLines/ms9yu01.mp3.transcription: Perhaps he needs some gentle persuasion.

RA2_VoiceLines/msaso01.mp3.transcription: Greetings Commander! Your forces need to invade the allied base and take over their battle lab. Get an engineer in there so we can pinpoint the location of their super weapon.

RA2_VoiceLines/msaso02.mp3.transcription: When your men are ready, I suggest you begin your assault here, Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/msaso03.mp3.transcription: This beach is well defended, but it is also the only place to land your troops effectively. Good luck, sir.

RA2_VoiceLines/msaso04.mp3.transcription: Aha! There it is! A weather control device. Luckily, Intel says it couldn't possibly be operational yet. Take it out, Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/msaso05.mp3.transcription: Apparently our intelligence was wrong, Apologies Commander. I am now downloading Schemaryx for a nuclear missile silo, so you can deal with his new threat.

RA2_VoiceLines/msayu01.mp3.transcription: Perhaps I could be of assistance.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbso01.mp3.transcription: Yuri will destroy us all. He must be stopped, no matter what the cost.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbso02.mp3.transcription: Commander, Yuri must be using an Iron Curtain device to make his troops invulnerable to attack, until indicates that the Iron Curtain effect cannot possibly be maintained for long.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbso05.mp3.transcription: Commander, looks like our nuclear asylum has been noticed. Yuri is sending a fleet of kirafs our way.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbso06.mp3.transcription: We had better get some flag cannons in place.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbyu01.mp3.transcription: You don't really think that war factor will help you defeat me, do you?

RA2_VoiceLines/msbyu02.mp3.transcription: So you are building a cure of? I'm impressed.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbyu03.mp3.transcription: I wouldn't build that psychic sensor if I were you.

RA2_VoiceLines/msbyu04.mp3.transcription: You are not really planning to nuke Mother Russia, are you?

RA2_VoiceLines/msbyu05.mp3.transcription: Tower drones are such mindless beasts. Why don't you train an engineer instead?

RA2_VoiceLines/mscso03.mp3.transcription: Now move up the coast. There is a small airfield there where we can build a base and reclaim our captured kit of ash ships.

RA2_VoiceLines/mscso04.mp3.transcription: They are using the Chronosphere to transport troops into our base. We cannot stop this assault. Attack soon, Commander, or we will be overrun.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds01.mp3.transcription: Good morning, Commander, and welcome to basic training. There's a war on, so we have to make this a crash course. In front of you is your battlefield control interface. With this interface, you can command any soldier on the field. Let's begin with the new recruit you see in the center of your screen. Move him away from his barracks and out into the field. Left-click on the soldier to select him. Then, left-click on empty ground to move him to that location. Try not to get him killed on the way to the shooting range.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds02.mp3.transcription: Notice how you can order your soldier to move into the dark area surrounding the base. This shroud indicates areas of the terrain that you have not yet explored.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds03.mp3.transcription: Now that you've mastered the difficult task of commanding a single soldier, try ordering around a squad. First, select all of the men by left clicking and holding down the mouse button. In this mode, you can drag a selection box around all of your men. Select all of the soldiers at once and order them east to the bridge.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds04.mp3.transcription: This bridge was destroyed yesterday when the Navy SEALs used it for demolition practice. An engineer is en route to repair it. When he arrives, left click on him to select him, then left click on the repair hut next to the bridge. Once the bridge is repaired, move your men across.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds05.mp3.transcription: This is the shooting range. Select your men by drag selecting a box around the group. Once selected, left click on the targets down range. This will order your men to fire at these targets. Destroy all of the targets.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds06.mp3.transcription: Excellent! Your men are good shots. There is a row of targets just out of range of your GIs. Double-click on one of your men. He will set himself up in a small defensive position. In this mode, he can fire at a greater range. Many units have special abilities like this. Now, order him to destroy the remaining targets.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds07.mp3.transcription: Notice that one of your men has a special symbol on him when he's selected. This unit is a veteran unit. Veterans are tougher, stronger, and can fire more accurately than ordinary soldiers. Double-click on the man who is set up in a defensive position to order him to move out. Now, order your men to move on up the road.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds08.mp3.transcription: In front of you is a derelict American grizzly battle tank. Order your men to destroy the crippled tank.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds09.mp3.transcription: It takes your men longer to destroy the tank than the targets at the rifle range. Regular soldiers are not efficient at destroying armored units. In turn, armored units may not be the most effective weapons for destroying dug-in infantry. Pick the right unit when facing enemies. Good job today. You've completed an important part of your training.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds10.mp3.transcription: Hurry up, Commander, you're boring me.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds11.mp3.transcription: Keep it moving, Commander. Your training has to go quickly. The Reds are already landing on our shores.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt1ds12.mp3.transcription: Commander, this is only one soldier. In a few days you will have to command armies. Now left click on him and then left click on open ground to get him moving out of the base.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds01.mp3.transcription: Today you will fight a mock battle against another commander. He will command the Red Team, you will command the Blue Team. Select your mobile construction vehicle by left clicking on it, then order it to move out of the base. Move out to the east and try to find some open ground.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds02.mp3.transcription: Your mobile construction vehicle is now in open ground. Double click on it to deploy a construction yard.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds03.mp3.transcription: Now that you have a construction yard, you can begin to build a base. On the right side of your screen, you can see that the icon for a power plant has appeared. Left click on that icon to start construction of the power plant. Notice how your remaining money decreases while the power plant is building. Each building has a cost to construct. When the power plant is done building, left click on its image, and then left click on an empty area near your construction yard. If you see red squares where you are trying to place it, then you are either trying to place the power plant too far away from your construction yard, or you are trying to build an uneven ground.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds04.mp3.transcription: Good, now your base has power. Notice the power indicator on the left side of your build bar. Each structure you build has a power cost. If your base runs short of power, some buildings will stop working and others will work inefficiently. Now it's time to build a refinery so you can begin harvesting. Ore and gems are harvested by your miners and converted to cash. Left click on the ore refinery icon. When your refinery is ready, place it in the same way you did with the power plant.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds05.mp3.transcription: Many buildings and units depend on one another. Placing a power plant allows you to build a refinery and barracks. Placing a barracks will allow you to train infantry. Left click on the barracks to start its construction. When it's finished, place it on the terrain just like you did with the refinery and power plant.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds06.mp3.transcription: On the right hand side of your screen, you should see a button that looks like a soldier. When you press that button, you will see the different types of soldiers that you can train. Right now, all you can train is a GI. Left click on the GI to start training him. Left click multiple times to train a series of GIs.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds07.mp3.transcription: Red team may attack soon. Your GIs are armed with rubber bullets for this mission. In real combat, they would, of course, be shooting real bullets.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds08.mp3.transcription: Here comes Red Team. Make me proud, Commander!

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds09.mp3.transcription: Red Team Strike Force has been defeated. Now build some more Soldiers Commander and when you feel you're ready, move them out onto the map. Find Red Team's Command Center and destroy it.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds10.mp3.transcription: You really weren't ready for Red Team were you, Commander? If this had happened against the Soviets, your base would now be in flames. Red Team will pull back to give you a chance to build some more troops.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds11.mp3.transcription: Good job, Commander. You've defeated the Red Team. Your basic training is complete.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds12.mp3.transcription: Your new Chrono minor will automatically begin to collect ore.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds14.mp3.transcription: Deploy your GIs near the entrance to your base for a better defense.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds15.mp3.transcription: Send your troops to garrison inside the barn for better protection from enemy fire.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds16.mp3.transcription: Send your troops to garrison inside civilian structures for better protection from enemy fire.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds17.mp3.transcription: Now is not the time for potty breaks, Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds19.mp3.transcription: Warning, the stench of a red team is in the air.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds20.mp3.transcription: Crates can be collected for special bonuses. This one contains a cash bonus.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds21.mp3.transcription: Your GIs can garrison inside many civilian structures. Select one of your GIs, then left-click on the barn to send them in. While garrisoned, your troops are protected from enemy fire. When the structure is severely damaged, all occupants will be ejected.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds22.mp3.transcription: Engineers can do more than just repair bridges. They can also repair most structures and capture many enemy structures.

RA2_VoiceLines/mt2ds23.mp3.transcription: To exit your soldiers from a civilian structure, select the structure, then click on it again.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma01.mp3.transcription: Welcome to World Wide Domination Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma02.mp3.transcription: updating new tactical data, please stand by.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma03.mp3.transcription: Allied forces have repelled numerous Soviet assaults.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma04.mp3.transcription: Soviet forces have taken control of a number of territories.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma06.mp3.transcription: This territory is now under Allied control.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma07.mp3.transcription: The Allies are winning the battle in this territory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma08.mp3.transcription: The Soviet Union forces control the majority of this territory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma09.mp3.transcription: Insufficient data. Neither forces control this territory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma10.mp3.transcription: Perhaps you should try another line of work, Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma11.mp3.transcription: To reaffirm the goal is to defeat the Soviet Union commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma12.mp3.transcription: The Allies are not pleased with your performance. The President would like a word with you.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma13.mp3.transcription: A decisive victory, Commander. The President will be pleased.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma14.mp3.transcription: Soviet forces have been decimated. Well done, Commander!

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma15.mp3.transcription: You do your reputation justice, Commander.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma16.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. This territory is now controlled by the Allies, evacuating to safe zone.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma17.mp3.transcription: Status report commander. This territory is now controlled by the Union, evacuating to safe zone.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma18.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. This territory is now controlled by the Soviet Union, relocating to new front-line position.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma19.mp3.transcription: Status report commander. This territory is now controlled by the Allies, relocating to new frontline position.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma20.mp3.transcription: Status Report Commander. We were unable to advance through this territory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma21.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. The battle is lost.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma22.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. We are victorious. All Soviet forces eliminated.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma23.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. We have stalemated with the Soviet Union.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma24.mp3.transcription: World Domination Progress Report Commander. We are gaining ground on several key fronts.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma25.mp3.transcription: World Domination Progress Report Commander. We were unable to stop the Soviet Union's assault on several key fronts.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoma26.mp3.transcription: World Domination Progress Report Commander. Nothing new to report, business as usual.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms03.mp3.transcription: The Soviets are losing ground. We may lose to the allies of this trend continues.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms04.mp3.transcription: The Soviets have made significant progress. The Allies are retreating.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms06.mp3.transcription: This sector is now under control of the Soviet Union.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms07.mp3.transcription: The Soviets have a firm grip in this territory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms08.mp3.transcription: We are in danger of losing this territory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms09.mp3.transcription: This territory is still under dispute.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms11.mp3.transcription: The Soviet Union does not take ineffective strategies lightly.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms12.mp3.transcription: You are not worthy to join the Soviet Union.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms13.mp3.transcription: Excellent. The Soviets go stronger, thanks to your victory.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms14.mp3.transcription: Romanov will be pleased with your efforts. You served the Union well.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms16.mp3.transcription: Status Report Commander. This territory is now controlled by the Allies, evacuating to safe zone.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms17.mp3.transcription: This territory is now controlled by the Allies.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms18.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. This territory is now controlled by the Soviet Union, relocating to new frontline position.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms19.mp3.transcription: Status report commander. We were unable to advance through this territory. Perhaps you are in need of further training.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms20.mp3.transcription: Status Report Commander. We have been defeated.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms21.mp3.transcription: Status report commander. We are victorious. All allied forces are vanquished.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms22.mp3.transcription: Status report, Commander. We have stalemated with the Allies.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms23.mp3.transcription: World Domination Progress Report Commander. Allied resistance is weakening on all fronts.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms24.mp3.transcription: World Domination Progress Report Commander. We are losing ground on all fronts.

RA2_VoiceLines/wdoms25.mp3.transcription: World Domination Progress Report Commander. We have been unable to advance our position.
